# Frontend UI Rules

- Keep components resilient with fallback UI for missing/failed data.
- Preserve accessibility basics: semantic controls, keyboard, labels, focus states.
- Do not break existing routes/navigation while redesigning UI.
- Prefer explicit loading/empty/error states over silent failures.

# Image/Media Handling

- For remote or mixed storage URLs, include graceful fallback when image render fails.
- If using optimized images, ensure host/domain rules are compatible.
- If fallback is used, explain trade-offs (performance vs reliability).

# Verification

- Confirm changed pages render without runtime errors.
- Confirm key user flows still work after UI changes.
